&gt; From your code:
&gt;
&gt; protected void addResponseContent (HttpMethod method, CrawlURI curi) {
&gt;
&gt; The HttpMethod parameter is passed to that method.  How to I get access
&gt; to the HttpMethod object from the CrawlURI object
&gt; that is passed to the innerProcess method of the Processor class?

Here is where the HttpMethod object gets added to the CrawlURI: 
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/fetcher/FetchHTTP.html#425.

In a processor, to get at the HttpMethod object via the current 
CrawlURI, do the inverse: CrawlURI#getObject(A_HTTP_TRANSACTION).

